    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a sales and product intelligence dashboard with a three-part user flow. 1) 'Overview' to introduce Olidia, its pros, cons, and side effects using interactive cards for quick learning. 2) 'Comparison' for a deep dive against competitors, featuring a dynamic table and bar chart that users control, empowering them to analyze the market. 3) 'Strategy' to provide actionable sales insights via a clean tabbed interface. This structure guides the user from product knowledge to market analysis and finally to sales application, making it a highly effective tool for a medical sales representative or a clinic owner. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: Olidia's key attributes (pros, cons, side effects) -> Goal: Inform -> Viz/Presentation Method: Interactive cards (HTML/CSS/JS) for focused, digestible information -> Interaction: Click-to-reveal details -> Justification: Breaks down complex information, improving retention and engagement. Report Info: Competitive landscape -> Goal: Compare -> Viz/Presentation Method: Dynamic HTML table paired with a Chart.js Bar Chart -> Interaction: Checkboxes to select products to compare, which dynamically updates both the table and the chart -> Justification: Provides a powerful, user-controlled analytical tool for direct comparison of both qualitative and quantitative data. Report Info: Sales tactics & positioning -> Goal: Organize & Educate -> Viz/Presentation Method: Tabbed content area (HTML/CSS/JS) -> Interaction: Click tabs to switch between sales pitch, result explanation, and competitive angles -> Justification: Organizes dense textual information into logical, easy-to-navigate sections. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
